line_1: " That doth the smallest Sin commit,
But as, some Errors still we must commit,
line_2: Nor Valour always ballanc'd is by Wit;

line_1: To our untainted faith shall they commit,
line_2: To win our grace, (rare argument of wit)

line_1: There's not a Sin that we commit,
line_2: But in thy dreadful Book 'tis writ,

line_1: Those actions, which he blush'd not to commit;
line_2: Would blush, should he be told, by Truth and Wit,

line_1: For when to Us she did commit
T' avoid great Errors, must the less commit,
line_2: As Men of Breeding, oft the Men of Wit
